Package com.foreach.across.modules.entity.registry.properties.binding

Class ChildEntityPropertyBindingContext

java.lang.Object
com.foreach.across.modules.entity.registry.properties.binding.ChildEntityPropertyBindingContext
All Implemented Interfaces:
EntityPropertyBindingContext, EntityPropertyBindingContextResolver
public final class ChildEntityPropertyBindingContext extends Object
Represents an EntityPropertyBindingContext for a child property of a parent EntityPropertyBindingContext. The property is represented by a EntityPropertyController that will be used to fetch the value from the parent binding context.
Since:
3.2.0
Author:
Arne Vandamme

      public EntityPropertyBindingContext resolvePropertyBindingContext(@NonNull @NonNull EntityPropertyDescriptor propertyDescriptor, boolean createIfPossible)
      Description copied from interface: EntityPropertyBindingContextResolver
      Resolve a EntityPropertyBindingContext for a specific child property. Optionally specify if the context should be created if it can be. When false only a pre-existing binding context would be returned. Useful for bulk fetching scenarios where an external process might create the binding context and then eagerly load the values.
